FBIS4-28621 "dreas113_d_94014" FBIS-EAS-94-113 Daily Report 11 Jun 1994 South Korea Holds Talks With Counterpart Han Holds Talks With Counterpart Han OW1106085494 Tokyo KYODO in English 0846 GMT 11 Jun 94 OW1106085494 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Seoul, June 11 KYODO -- The foreign ministers of Japan and South Korea confirmed Saturday that planned U.N. Security Council sanctions against North Korea over the nuclear standoff are aimed at encouraging Pyongyang to hold dialogue for a negotiated solution. The confirmation came at a meeting between Japanese Foreign Minister Koji Kakizawa and his South Korean counterpart Han Sung-chu held in Seoul, officials said. The two sides also pledged close bilateral cooperation in dealing with North Korea's suspected nuclear arms development program.
